5146void RGWRados::cls_obj_check_mtime(ObjectOperation& op, const real_time& mtime, bool high_precision_time, RGWCheckMTimeType type)
5147{
5148 cls_rgw_obj_check_mtime(op, mtime, high_precision_time, type);
5149}
5150
5151struct tombstone_entry {
5152 ceph::real_time mtime;
5153 uint32_t zone_short_id;
5154 uint64_t pg_ver;
5155
5156 tombstone_entry() = default;
5157 explicit tombstone_entry(const RGWObjState& state)
5158 : mtime(state.mtime), zone_short_id(state.zone_short_id),
5159 pg_ver(state.pg_ver) {}
5160};
5161
5168int RGWRados::Object::Delete::delete_obj(optional_yield y, const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp)
5169{
5170 RGWRados *store = target->get_store();
5171 rgw_obj& src_obj = target->get_obj();
5172 const string& instance = src_obj.key.instance;
5173 rgw_obj obj = src_obj;
5174
5175 if (instance == "null") {
5176 obj.key.instance.clear();
5177 }
5178
5179 bool explicit_marker_version = (!params.marker_version_id.empty());
5180
5181 if (params.versioning_status & BUCKET_VERSIONED || explicit_marker_version) {
5182 if (instance.empty() || explicit_marker_version) {
5183 rgw_obj marker = obj;
5184
5185 if (!params.marker_version_id.empty()) {
5186 if (params.marker_version_id != "null") {
5187 marker.key.set_instance(params.marker_version_id);
5188 }
5189 } else if ((params.versioning_status & BUCKET_VERSIONS_SUSPENDED) == 0) {
5190 store->gen_rand_obj_instance_name(&marker);
5191 }
5192
5193 result.version_id = marker.key.instance;
5194 if (result.version_id.empty())
5195 result.version_id = "null";
5196 result.delete_marker = true;
5197
5198 struct rgw_bucket_dir_entry_meta meta;
5199
5200 meta.owner = params.obj_owner.get_id().to_str();
5201 meta.owner_display_name = params.obj_owner.get_display_name();
5202
5203 if (real_clock::is_zero(params.mtime)) {
5204 meta.mtime = real_clock::now();
5205 } else {
5206 meta.mtime = params.mtime;
5207 }
5208
5209 int r = store->set_olh(dpp, target->get_ctx(), target->get_bucket_info(), marker, true, &meta, params.olh_epoch, params.unmod_since, params.high_precision_time, y, params.zones_trace);
5210 if (r < 0) {
5211 return r;
5212 }
5213 } else {
5214 rgw_bucket_dir_entry dirent;
5215
5216 int r = store->bi_get_instance(dpp, target->get_bucket_info(), obj, &dirent);
5217 if (r < 0) {
5218 return r;
5219 }
5220 result.delete_marker = dirent.is_delete_marker();
5221 r = store->unlink_obj_instance(dpp, target->get_ctx(), target->get_bucket_info(), obj, params.olh_epoch, y, params.zones_trace);
5222 if (r < 0) {
5223 return r;
5224 }
5225 result.version_id = instance;
5226 }
5227
5228 BucketShard *bs = nullptr;
5229 int r = target->get_bucket_shard(&bs, dpp);
5230 if (r < 0) {
5231 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << "failed to get BucketShard object: r=" << r << dendl;
5232 return r;
5233 }
5234
5235 r = store->svc.datalog_rados->add_entry(dpp, target->bucket_info, bs->shard_id);
5236 if (r < 0) {
5237 ldpp_dout(dpp, -1) << "ERROR: failed writing data log" << dendl;
5238 return r;
5239 }
5240
5241 return 0;
5242 }
5243
5244 rgw_rados_ref ref;
5245 int r = store->get_obj_head_ref(dpp, target->get_bucket_info(), obj, &ref);
5246 if (r < 0) {
5247 return r;
5248 }
5249
5250 RGWObjState *state;
5251 r = target->get_state(dpp, &state, false, y);
5252 if (r < 0)
5253 return r;
5254
5255 ObjectWriteOperation op;
5256
5257 if (!real_clock::is_zero(params.unmod_since)) {
5258 struct timespec ctime = ceph::real_clock::to_timespec(state->mtime);
5259 struct timespec unmod = ceph::real_clock::to_timespec(params.unmod_since);
5260 if (!params.high_precision_time) {
5261 ctime.tv_nsec = 0;
5262 unmod.tv_nsec = 0;
5263 }
5264
5265 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "If-UnModified-Since: " << params.unmod_since << " Last-Modified: " << ctime << dendl;
5266 if (ctime > unmod) {
5267 return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
5268 }
5269
5270 /* only delete object if mtime is less than or equal to params.unmod_since */
5271 store->cls_obj_check_mtime(op, params.unmod_since, params.high_precision_time, CLS_RGW_CHECK_TIME_MTIME_LE);
5272 }
5273 uint64_t obj_accounted_size = state->accounted_size;
5274
5275 if(params.abortmp) {
5276 obj_accounted_size = params.parts_accounted_size;
5277 }
5278
5279 if (!real_clock::is_zero(params.expiration_time)) {
5280 bufferlist bl;
5281 real_time delete_at;
5282
5283 if (state->get_attr(RGW_ATTR_DELETE_AT, bl)) {
5284 try {
5285 auto iter = bl.cbegin();
5286 decode(delete_at, iter);
5287 } catch (buffer::error& err) {
5288 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: couldn't decode RGW_ATTR_DELETE_AT" << dendl;
5289 return -EIO;
5290 }
5291
5292 if (params.expiration_time != delete_at) {
5293 return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
5294 }
5295 } else {
5296 return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
5297 }
5298 }
5299
5300 if (!state->exists) {
5301 target->invalidate_state();
5302 return -ENOENT;
5303 }
5304
5305 r = target->prepare_atomic_modification(dpp, op, false, NULL, NULL, NULL, true, false, y);
5306 if (r < 0)
5307 return r;
5308
5309 RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info = target->get_bucket_info();
5310
5311 RGWRados::Bucket bop(store, bucket_info);
5312 RGWRados::Bucket::UpdateIndex index_op(&bop, obj);
5313
5314 index_op.set_zones_trace(params.zones_trace);
5315 index_op.set_bilog_flags(params.bilog_flags);
5316
5317 r = index_op.prepare(dpp, CLS_RGW_OP_DEL, &state->write_tag, y);
5318 if (r < 0)
5319 return r;
5320
5321 store->remove_rgw_head_obj(op);
5322
5323 auto& ioctx = ref.pool.ioctx();
5324 r = rgw_rados_operate(dpp, ioctx, ref.obj.oid, &op, null_yield);
5325
5326 /* raced with another operation, object state is indeterminate */
5327 const bool need_invalidate = (r == -ECANCELED);
5328
5329 int64_t poolid = ioctx.get_id();
5330 if (r >= 0) {
5331 tombstone_cache_t *obj_tombstone_cache = store->get_tombstone_cache();
5332 if (obj_tombstone_cache) {
5333 tombstone_entry entry{*state};
5334 obj_tombstone_cache->add(obj, entry);
5335 }
5336 r = index_op.complete_del(dpp, poolid, ioctx.get_last_version(), state->mtime, params.remove_objs);
5337
5338 int ret = target->complete_atomic_modification(dpp);
5339 if (ret < 0) {
5340 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: complete_atomic_modification returned ret=" << ret << dendl;
5341 }
5342 /* other than that, no need to propagate error */
5343 } else {
5344 int ret = index_op.cancel(dpp, params.remove_objs);
5345 if (ret < 0) {
5346 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: index_op.cancel() returned ret=" << ret << dendl;
5347 }
5348 }
5349
5350 if (need_invalidate) {
5351 target->invalidate_state();
5352 }
5353
5354 if (r < 0)
5355 return r;
5356
5357 /* update quota cache */
5358 store->quota_handler->update_stats(params.bucket_owner, obj.bucket, -1, 0, obj_accounted_size);
5359
5360 return 0;
5361}
5362
5363int RGWRados::delete_obj(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
5364 RGWObjectCtx& obj_ctx,
5365 const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info,
5366 const rgw_obj& obj,
5367 int versioning_status, // versioning flags defined in enum RGWBucketFlags
5368 uint16_t bilog_flags,
5369 const real_time& expiration_time,
5370 rgw_zone_set *zones_trace)
5371{
5372 RGWRados::Object del_target(this, bucket_info, obj_ctx, obj);
5373 RGWRados::Object::Delete del_op(&del_target);
5374
5375 del_op.params.bucket_owner = bucket_info.owner;
5376 del_op.params.versioning_status = versioning_status;
5377 del_op.params.bilog_flags = bilog_flags;
5378 del_op.params.expiration_time = expiration_time;
5379 del_op.params.zones_trace = zones_trace;
5380
5381 return del_op.delete_obj(null_yield, dpp);
5382}
5383
5384int RGWRados::delete_raw_obj(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, const rgw_raw_obj& obj)
5385{
5386 rgw_rados_ref ref;
5387 int r = get_raw_obj_ref(dpp, obj, &ref);
5388 if (r < 0) {
5389 return r;
5390 }
5391
5392 ObjectWriteOperation op;
5393
5394 op.remove();
5395 r = rgw_rados_operate(dpp, ref.pool.ioctx(), ref.obj.oid, &op, null_yield);
5396 if (r < 0)
5397 return r;
5398
5399 return 0;
5400}
5401
5402int RGWRados::delete_obj_index(const rgw_obj& obj, ceph::real_time mtime, const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp)
5403{
5404 std::string oid, key;
5405 get_obj_bucket_and_oid_loc(obj, oid, key);
5406
5407 auto obj_ctx = svc.sysobj->init_obj_ctx();
5408
5409 RGWBucketInfo bucket_info;
5410 int ret = get_bucket_instance_info(obj_ctx, obj.bucket, bucket_info, NULL, NULL, null_yield, dpp);
5411 if (ret < 0) {
5412 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: " << __func__ << "() get_bucket_instance_info(bucket=" << obj.bucket << ") returned ret=" << ret << dendl;
5413 return ret;
5414 }
5415
5416 RGWRados::Bucket bop(this, bucket_info);
5417 RGWRados::Bucket::UpdateIndex index_op(&bop, obj);
5418
5419 return index_op.complete_del(dpp, -1 /* pool */, 0, mtime, NULL);
5420}
5421
5422static void generate_fake_tag(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, rgw::sal::Store* store, map<string, bufferlist>& attrset, RGWObjManifest& manifest, bufferlist& manifest_bl, bufferlist& tag_bl)
5423{
5424 string tag;
5425
5426 RGWObjManifest::obj_iterator mi = manifest.obj_begin(dpp);
5427 if (mi != manifest.obj_end(dpp)) {
5428 if (manifest.has_tail()) // first object usually points at the head, let's skip to a more unique part
5429 ++mi;
5430 rgw::sal::RadosStore* rstore = dynamic_cast<rgw::sal::RadosStore*>(store);
5431 tag = mi.get_location().get_raw_obj(rstore).oid;
5432 tag.append("_");
5433 }
5434
5435 unsigned char md5[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE];
5436 char md5_str[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE * 2 + 1];
5437 MD5 hash;
5438 // Allow use of MD5 digest in FIPS mode for non-cryptographic purposes
5439 hash.SetFlags(EVP_MD_CTX_FLAG_NON_FIPS_ALLOW);
5440 hash.Update((const unsigned char *)manifest_bl.c_str(), manifest_bl.length());
5441
5442 map<string, bufferlist>::iterator iter = attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_ETAG);
5443 if (iter != attrset.end()) {
5444 bufferlist& bl = iter->second;
5445 hash.Update((const unsigned char *)bl.c_str(), bl.length());
5446 }
5447
5448 hash.Final(md5);
5449 buf_to_hex(md5, CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE, md5_str);
5450 tag.append(md5_str);
5451
5452 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "generate_fake_tag new tag=" << tag << dendl;
5453
5454 tag_bl.append(tag.c_str(), tag.size() + 1);
5455}
5456
5457static bool is_olh(map<string, bufferlist>& attrs)
5458{
5459 map<string, bufferlist>::iterator iter = attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_OLH_INFO);
5460 return (iter != attrs.end());
5461}
5462
5463static bool has_olh_tag(map<string, bufferlist>& attrs)
5464{
5465 map<string, bufferlist>::iterator iter = attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_OLH_ID_TAG);
5466 return (iter != attrs.end());
5467}
5468
5469int RGWRados::get_olh_target_state(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWObjectCtx& obj_ctx, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, const rgw_obj& obj,
5470 RGWObjState *olh_state, RGWObjState **target_state, optional_yield y)
5471{
5472 ceph_assert(olh_state->is_olh);
5473
5474 rgw_obj target;
5475 int r = RGWRados::follow_olh(dpp, bucket_info, obj_ctx, olh_state, obj, &target); /* might return -EAGAIN */
5476 if (r < 0) {
5477 return r;
5478 }
5479 r = get_obj_state(dpp, &obj_ctx, bucket_info, target, target_state, false, y);
5480 if (r < 0) {
5481 return r;
5482 }
5483
5484 return 0;
5485}
5486
5487int RGWRados::get_obj_state_impl(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWObjectCtx *rctx, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, const rgw_obj& obj,
5488 RGWObjState **state, bool follow_olh, optional_yield y, bool assume_noent)
5489{
5490 if (obj.empty()) {
5491 return -EINVAL;
5492 }
5493
5494 bool need_follow_olh = follow_olh && obj.key.instance.empty();
5495
5496 RGWObjState *s = rctx->get_state(obj);
5497 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "get_obj_state: rctx=" << (void *)rctx << " obj=" << obj << " state=" << (void *)s << " s->prefetch_data=" << s->prefetch_data << dendl;
5498 *state = s;
5499 if (s->has_attrs) {
5500 if (s->is_olh && need_follow_olh) {
5501 return get_olh_target_state(dpp, *rctx, bucket_info, obj, s, state, y);
5502 }
5503 return 0;
5504 }
5505
5506 s->obj = obj;
5507
5508 rgw_raw_obj raw_obj;
5509 obj_to_raw(bucket_info.placement_rule, obj, &raw_obj);
5510
5511 int r = -ENOENT;
5512
5513 if (!assume_noent) {
5514 r = RGWRados::raw_obj_stat(dpp, raw_obj, &s->size, &s->mtime, &s->epoch, &s->attrset, (s->prefetch_data ? &s->data : NULL), NULL, y);
5515 }
5516
5517 if (r == -ENOENT) {
5518 s->exists = false;
5519 s->has_attrs = true;
5520 tombstone_entry entry;
5521 if (obj_tombstone_cache && obj_tombstone_cache->find(obj, entry)) {
5522 s->mtime = entry.mtime;
5523 s->zone_short_id = entry.zone_short_id;
5524 s->pg_ver = entry.pg_ver;
5525 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << __func__ << "(): found obj in tombstone cache: obj=" << obj
5526 << " mtime=" << s->mtime << " pgv=" << s->pg_ver << dendl;
5527 } else {
5528 s->mtime = real_time();
5529 }
5530 return 0;
5531 }
5532 if (r < 0)
5533 return r;
5534
5535 s->exists = true;
5536 s->has_attrs = true;
5537 s->accounted_size = s->size;
5538
5539 auto iter = s->attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_ETAG);
5540 if (iter != s->attrset.end()) {
5541 /* get rid of extra null character at the end of the etag, as we used to store it like that */
5542 bufferlist& bletag = iter->second;
5543 if (bletag.length() > 0 && bletag[bletag.length() - 1] == '\0') {
5544 bufferlist newbl;
5545 bletag.splice(0, bletag.length() - 1, &newbl);
5546 bletag = std::move(newbl);
5547 }
5548 }
5549
5550 iter = s->attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_COMPRESSION);
5551 const bool compressed = (iter != s->attrset.end());
5552 if (compressed) {
5553 // use uncompressed size for accounted_size
5554 try {
5555 RGWCompressionInfo info;
5556 auto p = iter->second.cbegin();
5557 decode(info, p);
5558 s->accounted_size = info.orig_size;
5559 } catch (buffer::error&) {
5560 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: could not decode compression info for object: " << obj << dendl;
5561 return -EIO;
5562 }
5563 }
5564
5565 iter = s->attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_SHADOW_OBJ);
5566 if (iter != s->attrset.end()) {
5567 bufferlist bl = iter->second;
5568 bufferlist::iterator it = bl.begin();
5569 it.copy(bl.length(), s->shadow_obj);
5570 s->shadow_obj[bl.length()] = '\0';
5571 }
5572 s->obj_tag = s->attrset[RGW_ATTR_ID_TAG];
5573 auto ttiter = s->attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_TAIL_TAG);
5574 if (ttiter != s->attrset.end()) {
5575 s->tail_tag = s->attrset[RGW_ATTR_TAIL_TAG];
5576 }
5577
5578 bufferlist manifest_bl = s->attrset[RGW_ATTR_MANIFEST];
5579 if (manifest_bl.length()) {
5580 auto miter = manifest_bl.cbegin();
5581 try {
5582 s->manifest.emplace();
5583 decode(*s->manifest, miter);
5584 s->manifest->set_head(bucket_info.placement_rule, obj, s->size); /* patch manifest to reflect the head we just read, some manifests might be
5585 broken due to old bugs */
5586 s->size = s->manifest->get_obj_size();
5587 if (!compressed)
5588 s->accounted_size = s->size;
5589 } catch (buffer::error& err) {
5590 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: couldn't decode manifest" << dendl;
5591 return -EIO;
5592 }
5593 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "manifest: total_size = " << s->manifest->get_obj_size() << dendl;
5594 if (cct->_conf->subsys.should_gather<ceph_subsys_rgw, 20>() && \
5595 s->manifest->has_explicit_objs()) {
5596 RGWObjManifest::obj_iterator mi;
5597 for (mi = s->manifest->obj_begin(dpp); mi != s->manifest->obj_end(dpp); ++mi) {
5598 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "manifest: ofs=" << mi.get_ofs() << " loc=" << mi.get_location().get_raw_obj(store) << dendl;
5599 }
5600 }
5601
5602 if (!s->obj_tag.length()) {
5603 /*
5604 * Uh oh, something's wrong, object with manifest should have tag. Let's
5605 * create one out of the manifest, would be unique
5606 */
5607 generate_fake_tag(dpp, store, s->attrset, *s->manifest, manifest_bl, s->obj_tag);
5608 s->fake_tag = true;
5609 }
5610 }
5611 map<string, bufferlist>::iterator aiter = s->attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_PG_VER);
5612 if (aiter != s->attrset.end()) {
5613 bufferlist& pg_ver_bl = aiter->second;
5614 if (pg_ver_bl.length()) {
5615 auto pgbl = pg_ver_bl.cbegin();
5616 try {
5617 decode(s->pg_ver, pgbl);
5618 } catch (buffer::error& err) {
5619 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: couldn't decode pg ver attr for object " << s->obj << ", non-critical error, ignoring" << dendl;
5620 }
5621 }
5622 }
5623 aiter = s->attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_SOURCE_ZONE);
5624 if (aiter != s->attrset.end()) {
5625 bufferlist& zone_short_id_bl = aiter->second;
5626 if (zone_short_id_bl.length()) {
5627 auto zbl = zone_short_id_bl.cbegin();
5628 try {
5629 decode(s->zone_short_id, zbl);
5630 } catch (buffer::error& err) {
5631 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: couldn't decode zone short id attr for object " << s->obj << ", non-critical error, ignoring" << dendl;
5632 }
5633 }
5634 }
5635 if (s->obj_tag.length()) {
5636 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "get_obj_state: setting s->obj_tag to " << s->obj_tag.c_str() << dendl;
5637 } else {
5638 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "get_obj_state: s->obj_tag was set empty" << dendl;
5639 }
5640
5641 /* an object might not be olh yet, but could have olh id tag, so we should set it anyway if
5642 * it exist, and not only if is_olh() returns true
5643 */
5644 iter = s->attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_OLH_ID_TAG);
5645 if (iter != s->attrset.end()) {
5646 s->olh_tag = iter->second;
5647 }
5648
5649 if (is_olh(s->attrset)) {
5650 s->is_olh = true;
5651
5652 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << __func__ << ": setting s->olh_tag to " << string(s->olh_tag.c_str(), s->olh_tag.length()) << dendl;
5653
5654 if (need_follow_olh) {
5655 return get_olh_target_state(dpp, *rctx, bucket_info, obj, s, state, y);
5656 } else if (obj.key.have_null_instance() && !s->manifest) {
5657 // read null version, and the head object only have olh info
5658 s->exists = false;
5659 return -ENOENT;
5660 }
5661 }
5662
5663 return 0;
5664}
5665
5666int RGWRados::get_obj_state(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWObjectCtx *rctx, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, const rgw_obj& obj, RGWObjState **state,
5667 bool follow_olh, optional_yield y, bool assume_noent)
5668{
5669 int ret;
5670
5671 do {
5672 ret = get_obj_state_impl(dpp, rctx, bucket_info, obj, state, follow_olh, y, assume_noent);
5673 } while (ret == -EAGAIN);
5674
5675 return ret;
5676}
5677
5678int RGWRados::Object::get_manifest(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWObjManifest **pmanifest, optional_yield y)
5679{
5680 RGWObjState *astate;
5681 int r = get_state(dpp, &astate, true, y);
5682 if (r < 0) {
5683 return r;
5684 }
5685
5686 *pmanifest = &(*astate->manifest);
5687
5688 return 0;
5689}
5690
5691int RGWRados::Object::Read::get_attr(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, const char *name, bufferlist& dest, optional_yield y)
5692{
5693 RGWObjState *state;
5694 int r = source->get_state(dpp, &state, true, y);
5695 if (r < 0)
5696 return r;
5697 if (!state->exists)
5698 return -ENOENT;
5699 if (!state->get_attr(name, dest))
5700 return -ENODATA;
5701
5702 return 0;
5703}
5704
5705int RGWRados::Object::Stat::stat_async(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp)
5706{
5707 RGWObjectCtx& ctx = source->get_ctx();
5708 rgw_obj& obj = source->get_obj();
5709 RGWRados *store = source->get_store();
5710
5711 RGWObjState *s = ctx.get_state(obj); /* calling this one directly because otherwise a sync request will be sent */
5712 result.obj = obj;
5713 if (s->has_attrs) {
5714 state.ret = 0;
5715 result.size = s->size;
5716 result.mtime = ceph::real_clock::to_timespec(s->mtime);
5717 result.attrs = s->attrset;
5718 result.manifest = s->manifest;
5719 return 0;
5720 }
5721
5722 string oid;
5723 string loc;
5724 get_obj_bucket_and_oid_loc(obj, oid, loc);
5725
5726 int r = store->get_obj_head_ioctx(dpp, source->get_bucket_info(), obj, &state.io_ctx);
5727 if (r < 0) {
5728 return r;
5729 }
5730
5731 librados::ObjectReadOperation op;
5732 op.stat2(&result.size, &result.mtime, NULL);
5733 op.getxattrs(&result.attrs, NULL);
5734 state.completion = librados::Rados::aio_create_completion(nullptr, nullptr);
5735 state.io_ctx.locator_set_key(loc);
5736 r = state.io_ctx.aio_operate(oid, state.completion, &op, NULL);
5737 if (r < 0) {
5738 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << __func__
5739 << ": ERROR: aio_operate() returned ret=" << r
5740 << dendl;
5741 return r;
5742 }
5743
5744 return 0;
5745}
5746
5747
5748int RGWRados::Object::Stat::wait(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp)
5749{
5750 if (!state.completion) {
5751 return state.ret;
5752 }
5753
5754 state.completion->wait_for_complete();
5755 state.ret = state.completion->get_return_value();
5756 state.completion->release();
5757
5758 if (state.ret != 0) {
5759 return state.ret;
5760 }
5761
5762 return finish(dpp);
5763}
5764
5765int RGWRados::Object::Stat::finish(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp)
5766{
5767 map<string, bufferlist>::iterator iter = result.attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_MANIFEST);
5768 if (iter != result.attrs.end()) {
5769 bufferlist& bl = iter->second;
5770 auto biter = bl.cbegin();
5771 try {
5772 result.manifest.emplace();
5773 decode(*result.manifest, biter);
5774 } catch (buffer::error& err) {
5775 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: " << __func__ << ": failed to decode manifest" << dendl;
5776 return -EIO;
5777 }
5778 }
5779
5780 return 0;
5781}
5782
5783int RGWRados::append_atomic_test(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWObjectCtx *rctx,
5784 const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, const rgw_obj& obj,
5785 ObjectOperation& op, RGWObjState **pstate, optional_yield y)
5786{
5787 if (!rctx)
5788 return 0;
5789
5790 int r = get_obj_state(dpp, rctx, bucket_info, obj, pstate, false, y);
5791 if (r < 0)
5792 return r;
5793
5794 return append_atomic_test(dpp, *pstate, op);
5795}
5796
5797int RGWRados::append_atomic_test(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
5798 const RGWObjState* state,
5799 librados::ObjectOperation& op)
5800{
5801 if (!state->is_atomic) {
5802 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "state for obj=" << state->obj << " is not atomic, not appending atomic test" << dendl;
5803 return 0;
5804 }
5805
5806 if (state->obj_tag.length() > 0 && !state->fake_tag) {// check for backward compatibility
5807 op.cmpxattr(RGW_ATTR_ID_TAG, LIBRADOS_CMPXATTR_OP_EQ, state->obj_tag);
5808 } else {
5809 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "state->obj_tag is empty, not appending atomic test" << dendl;
5810 }
5811 return 0;
5812}
5813
5814int RGWRados::Object::get_state(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWObjState **pstate, bool follow_olh, optional_yield y, bool assume_noent)
5815{
5816 return store->get_obj_state(dpp, &ctx, bucket_info, obj, pstate, follow_olh, y, assume_noent);
5817}
5818
5819void RGWRados::Object::invalidate_state()
5820{
5821 ctx.invalidate(obj);
5822}
5823
5824int RGWRados::Object::prepare_atomic_modification(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
5825 ObjectWriteOperation& op, bool reset_obj, const string *ptag,
5826 const char *if_match, const char *if_nomatch, bool removal_op,
5827 bool modify_tail, optional_yield y)
5828{
5829 int r = get_state(dpp, &state, false, y);
5830 if (r < 0)
5831 return r;
5832
5833 bool need_guard = ((state->manifest) || (state->obj_tag.length() != 0) ||
5834 if_match != NULL || if_nomatch != NULL) &&
5835 (!state->fake_tag);
5836
5837 if (!state->is_atomic) {
5838 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "prepare_atomic_modification: state is not atomic. state=" << (void *)state << dendl;
5839
5840 if (reset_obj) {
5841 op.create(false);
5842 store->remove_rgw_head_obj(op); // we're not dropping reference here, actually removing object
5843 }
5844
5845 return 0;
5846 }
5847
5848 if (need_guard) {
5849 /* first verify that the object wasn't replaced under */
5850 if (if_nomatch == NULL || strcmp(if_nomatch, "*") != 0) {
5851 op.cmpxattr(RGW_ATTR_ID_TAG, LIBRADOS_CMPXATTR_OP_EQ, state->obj_tag);
5852 // FIXME: need to add FAIL_NOTEXIST_OK for racing deletion
5853 }
5854
5855 if (if_match) {
5856 if (strcmp(if_match, "*") == 0) {
5857 // test the object is existing
5858 if (!state->exists) {
5859 return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
5860 }
5861 } else {
5862 bufferlist bl;
5863 if (!state->get_attr(RGW_ATTR_ETAG, bl) ||
5864 strncmp(if_match, bl.c_str(), bl.length()) != 0) {
5865 return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
5866 }
5867 }
5868 }
5869
5870 if (if_nomatch) {
5871 if (strcmp(if_nomatch, "*") == 0) {
5872 // test the object is NOT existing
5873 if (state->exists) {
5874 return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
5875 }
5876 } else {
5877 bufferlist bl;
5878 if (!state->get_attr(RGW_ATTR_ETAG, bl) ||
5879 strncmp(if_nomatch, bl.c_str(), bl.length()) == 0) {
5880 return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
5881 }
5882 }
5883 }
5884 }
5885
5886 if (reset_obj) {
5887 if (state->exists) {
5888 op.create(false);
5889 store->remove_rgw_head_obj(op);
5890 } else {
5891 op.create(true);
5892 }
5893 }
5894
5895 if (removal_op) {
5896 /* the object is being removed, no need to update its tag */
5897 return 0;
5898 }
5899
5900 if (ptag) {
5901 state->write_tag = *ptag;
5902 } else {
5903 append_rand_alpha(store->ctx(), state->write_tag, state->write_tag, 32);
5904 }
5905 bufferlist bl;
5906 bl.append(state->write_tag.c_str(), state->write_tag.size() + 1);
5907
5908 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "setting object write_tag=" << state->write_tag << dendl;
5909
5910 op.setxattr(RGW_ATTR_ID_TAG, bl);
5911 if (modify_tail) {
5912 op.setxattr(RGW_ATTR_TAIL_TAG, bl);
5913 }
5914
5915 return 0;
5916}
5917
5926int RGWRados::set_attr(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, void *ctx, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, rgw_obj& obj, const char *name, bufferlist& bl)
5927{
5928 map<string, bufferlist> attrs;
5929 attrs[name] = bl;
5930 return set_attrs(dpp, ctx, bucket_info, obj, attrs, NULL, null_yield);
5931}
5932
5933int RGWRados::set_attrs(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, void *ctx, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, rgw_obj& src_obj,
5934 map<string, bufferlist>& attrs,
5935 map<string, bufferlist>* rmattrs,
5936 optional_yield y)
5937{
5938 rgw_obj obj = src_obj;
5939 if (obj.key.instance == "null") {
5940 obj.key.instance.clear();
5941 }
5942
5943 rgw_rados_ref ref;
5944 int r = get_obj_head_ref(dpp, bucket_info, obj, &ref);
5945 if (r < 0) {
5946 return r;
5947 }
5948 RGWObjectCtx *rctx = static_cast<RGWObjectCtx *>(ctx);
5949
5950 ObjectWriteOperation op;
5951 RGWObjState *state = NULL;
5952
5953 r = append_atomic_test(dpp, rctx, bucket_info, obj, op, &state, y);
5954 if (r < 0)
5955 return r;
5956
5957 // ensure null version object exist
5958 if (src_obj.key.instance == "null" && !state->manifest) {
5959 return -ENOENT;
5960 }
5961
5962 map<string, bufferlist>::iterator iter;
5963 if (rmattrs) {
5964 for (iter = rmattrs->begin(); iter != rmattrs->end(); ++iter) {
5965 const string& name = iter->first;
5966 op.rmxattr(name.c_str());
5967 }
5968 }
5969
5970 const rgw_bucket& bucket = obj.bucket;
5971
5972 for (iter = attrs.begin(); iter != attrs.end(); ++iter) {
5973 const string& name = iter->first;
5974 bufferlist& bl = iter->second;
5975
5976 if (!bl.length())
5977 continue;
5978
5979 op.setxattr(name.c_str(), bl);
5980
5981 if (name.compare(RGW_ATTR_DELETE_AT) == 0) {
5982 real_time ts;
5983 try {
5984 decode(ts, bl);
5985
5986 rgw_obj_index_key obj_key;
5987 obj.key.get_index_key(&obj_key);
5988
5989 obj_expirer->hint_add(dpp, ts, bucket.tenant, bucket.name, bucket.bucket_id, obj_key);
5990 } catch (buffer::error& err) {
5991 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: failed to decode " RGW_ATTR_DELETE_AT << " attr" << dendl;
5992 }
5993 }
5994 }
5995
5996 if (!op.size())
5997 return 0;
5998
5999 RGWObjectCtx obj_ctx(this->store);
6000
6001 bufferlist bl;
6002 RGWRados::Bucket bop(this, bucket_info);
6003 RGWRados::Bucket::UpdateIndex index_op(&bop, obj);
6004
6005 if (state) {
6006 string tag;
6007 append_rand_alpha(cct, tag, tag, 32);
6008 state->write_tag = tag;
6009 r = index_op.prepare(dpp, CLS_RGW_OP_ADD, &state->write_tag, y);
6010
6011 if (r < 0)
6012 return r;
6013
6014 bl.append(tag.c_str(), tag.size() + 1);
6015 op.setxattr(RGW_ATTR_ID_TAG, bl);
6016 }
6017
6018
6019 real_time mtime = real_clock::now();
6020 struct timespec mtime_ts = real_clock::to_timespec(mtime);
6021 op.mtime2(&mtime_ts);
6022 auto& ioctx = ref.pool.ioctx();
6023 r = rgw_rados_operate(dpp, ioctx, ref.obj.oid, &op, null_yield);
6024 if (state) {
6025 if (r >= 0) {
6026 bufferlist acl_bl = attrs[RGW_ATTR_ACL];
6027 bufferlist etag_bl = attrs[RGW_ATTR_ETAG];
6028 bufferlist content_type_bl = attrs[RGW_ATTR_CONTENT_TYPE];
6029 string etag = rgw_bl_str(etag_bl);
6030 string content_type = rgw_bl_str(content_type_bl);
6031 string storage_class;
6032 auto iter = attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_STORAGE_CLASS);
6033 if (iter != attrs.end()) {
6034 storage_class = rgw_bl_str(iter->second);
6035 }
6036 uint64_t epoch = ioctx.get_last_version();
6037 int64_t poolid = ioctx.get_id();
6038 r = index_op.complete(dpp, poolid, epoch, state->size, state->accounted_size,
6039 mtime, etag, content_type, storage_class, &acl_bl,
6040 RGWObjCategory::Main, NULL);
6041 } else {
6042 int ret = index_op.cancel(dpp, nullptr);
6043 if (ret < 0) {
6044 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: complete_update_index_cancel() returned ret=" << ret << dendl;
6045 }
6046 }
6047 }
6048 if (r < 0)
6049 return r;
6050
6051 if (state) {
6052 state->obj_tag.swap(bl);
6053 if (rmattrs) {
6054 for (iter = rmattrs->begin(); iter != rmattrs->end(); ++iter) {
6055 state->attrset.erase(iter->first);
6056 }
6057 }
6058
6059 for (iter = attrs.begin(); iter != attrs.end(); ++iter) {
6060 state->attrset[iter->first] = iter->second;
6061 }
6062
6063 auto iter = state->attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_ID_TAG);
6064 if (iter != state->attrset.end()) {
6065 iter->second = state->obj_tag;
6066 }
6067 }
6068
6069 return 0;
6070}
6071
6072int RGWRados::Object::Read::prepare(optional_yield y, const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp)
6073{
6074 RGWRados *store = source->get_store();
6075 CephContext *cct = store->ctx();
6076
6077 bufferlist etag;
6078
6079 map<string, bufferlist>::iterator iter;
6080
6081 RGWObjState *astate;
6082 int r = source->get_state(dpp, &astate, true, y);
6083 if (r < 0)
6084 return r;
6085
6086 if (!astate->exists) {
6087 return -ENOENT;
6088 }
6089
6090 const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info = source->get_bucket_info();
6091
6092 state.obj = astate->obj;
6093 store->obj_to_raw(bucket_info.placement_rule, state.obj, &state.head_obj);
6094
6095 state.cur_pool = state.head_obj.pool;
6096 state.cur_ioctx = &state.io_ctxs[state.cur_pool];
6097
6098 r = store->get_obj_head_ioctx(dpp, bucket_info, state.obj, state.cur_ioctx);
6099 if (r < 0) {
6100 return r;
6101 }
6102 if (params.target_obj) {
6103 *params.target_obj = state.obj;
6104 }
6105 if (params.attrs) {
6106 *params.attrs = astate->attrset;
6107 if (cct->_conf->subsys.should_gather<ceph_subsys_rgw, 20>()) {
6108 for (iter = params.attrs->begin(); iter != params.attrs->end(); ++iter) {
6109 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "Read xattr rgw_rados: " << iter->first << dendl;
6110 }
6111 }
6112 }
6113
6114 /* Convert all times go GMT to make them compatible */
6115 if (conds.mod_ptr || conds.unmod_ptr) {
6116 obj_time_weight src_weight;
6117 src_weight.init(astate);
6118 src_weight.high_precision = conds.high_precision_time;
6119
6120 obj_time_weight dest_weight;
6121 dest_weight.high_precision = conds.high_precision_time;
6122
6123 if (conds.mod_ptr && !conds.if_nomatch) {
6124 dest_weight.init(*conds.mod_ptr, conds.mod_zone_id, conds.mod_pg_ver);
6125 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "If-Modified-Since: " << dest_weight << " Last-Modified: " << src_weight << dendl;
6126 if (!(dest_weight < src_weight)) {
6127 return -ERR_NOT_MODIFIED;
6128 }
6129 }
6130
6131 if (conds.unmod_ptr && !conds.if_match) {
6132 dest_weight.init(*conds.unmod_ptr, conds.mod_zone_id, conds.mod_pg_ver);
6133 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "If-UnModified-Since: " << dest_weight << " Last-Modified: " << src_weight << dendl;
6134 if (dest_weight < src_weight) {
6135 return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
6136 }
6137 }
6138 }
6139 if (conds.if_match || conds.if_nomatch) {
6140 r = get_attr(dpp, RGW_ATTR_ETAG, etag, y);
6141 if (r < 0)
6142 return r;
6143
6144 if (conds.if_match) {
6145 string if_match_str = rgw_string_unquote(conds.if_match);
6146 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "ETag: " << string(etag.c_str(), etag.length()) << " " << " If-Match: " << if_match_str << dendl;
6147 if (if_match_str.compare(0, etag.length(), etag.c_str(), etag.length()) != 0) {
6148 return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
6149 }
6150 }
6151
6152 if (conds.if_nomatch) {
6153 string if_nomatch_str = rgw_string_unquote(conds.if_nomatch);
6154 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "ETag: " << string(etag.c_str(), etag.length()) << " " << " If-NoMatch: " << if_nomatch_str << dendl;
6155 if (if_nomatch_str.compare(0, etag.length(), etag.c_str(), etag.length()) == 0) {
6156 return -ERR_NOT_MODIFIED;
6157 }
6158 }
6159 }
6160
6161 if (params.obj_size)
6162 *params.obj_size = astate->size;
6163 if (params.lastmod)
6164 *params.lastmod = astate->mtime;
6165
6166 return 0;
6167}
6168
6169int RGWRados::Object::Read::range_to_ofs(uint64_t obj_size, int64_t &ofs, int64_t &end)
6170{
6171 if (ofs < 0) {
6172 ofs += obj_size;
6173 if (ofs < 0)
6174 ofs = 0;
6175 end = obj_size - 1;
6176 } else if (end < 0) {
6177 end = obj_size - 1;
6178 }
6179
6180 if (obj_size > 0) {
6181 if (ofs >= (off_t)obj_size) {
6182 return -ERANGE;
6183 }
6184 if (end >= (off_t)obj_size) {
6185 end = obj_size - 1;
6186 }
6187 }
6188 return 0;
6189}
6190
6191int RGWRados::Bucket::UpdateIndex::guard_reshard(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, BucketShard **pbs, std::function<int(BucketShard *)> call)
6192{
6193 RGWRados *store = target->get_store();
6194 BucketShard *bs = nullptr;
6195 int r;
6196
6197#define NUM_RESHARD_RETRIES 10
6198 for (int i = 0; i < NUM_RESHARD_RETRIES; ++i) {
6199 int ret = get_bucket_shard(&bs, dpp);
6200 if (ret < 0) {
6201 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << "failed to get BucketShard object: ret=" << ret << dendl;
6202 return ret;
6203 }
6204
6205 r = call(bs);
6206 if (r != -ERR_BUSY_RESHARDING && r != -ENOENT) {
6207 break;
6208 }
6209
6210 std::string new_bucket_id;
6211
6212 // different logic depending whether resharding completed or is
6213 // underway
6214
6215 if (r == -ENOENT) { // case where resharding must have completed
6216 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) <<
6217 "NOTICE: resharding operation recently completed, invalidating "
6218 "old BucketInfo" << dendl;
6219
6220 r = store->fetch_new_bucket_id(target->bucket_info,
6221 nullptr,
6222 new_bucket_id, dpp);
6223 if (r == -ENOENT) {
6224 // apparently this op raced with a bucket deletion
6225 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "WARNING: " << __func__ <<
6226 " unable to fetch bucket_id, apparently due to race "
6227 "with deletion of bucket: " <<
6228 target->bucket_info.bucket.get_key() << dendl;
6229 return -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
6230 } else if (r < 0) {
6231 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: " << __func__ <<
6232 " unable to refresh stale bucket_id after reshard; r=" <<
6233 r << dendl;
6234 return r;
6235 }
6236 } else { // must have been resharding at the time
6237 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "NOTICE: resharding operation on bucket index detected, blocking" << dendl;
6238
6239 r = store->block_while_resharding(bs, &new_bucket_id,
6240 target->bucket_info, null_yield, dpp);
6241 if (r == -ERR_BUSY_RESHARDING) {
6242 continue;
6243 }
6244 if (r < 0) {
6245 return r;
6246 }
6247
6248 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "reshard completion identified, new_bucket_id=" << new_bucket_id << dendl;
6249 i = 0; /* resharding is finished, make sure we can retry */
6250 }
6251
6252 // common portion -- finished resharding either way
6253
6254 r = target->update_bucket_id(new_bucket_id, dpp);
6255 if (r < 0) {
6256 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: update_bucket_id() new_bucket_id=" << new_bucket_id << " returned r=" << r << dendl;
6257 return r;
6258 }
6259
6260 invalidate_bs();
6261 } // for loop
6262
6263 if (r < 0) {
6264 return r;
6265 }
6266
6267 if (pbs) {
6268 *pbs = bs;
6269 }
6270
6271 return 0;
6272}
6273
6274int RGWRados::Bucket::UpdateIndex::prepare(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWModifyOp op, const string *write_tag, optional_yield y)
6275{
6276 if (blind) {
6277 return 0;
6278 }
6279 RGWRados *store = target->get_store();
6280
6281 if (write_tag && write_tag->length()) {
6282 optag = string(write_tag->c_str(), write_tag->length());
6283 } else {
6284 if (optag.empty()) {
6285 append_rand_alpha(store->ctx(), optag, optag, 32);
6286 }
6287 }
6288
6289 int r = guard_reshard(dpp, nullptr, [&](BucketShard *bs) -> int {
6290 return store->cls_obj_prepare_op(dpp, *bs, op, optag, obj, bilog_flags, y, zones_trace);
6291 });
6292
6293 if (r < 0) {
6294 return r;
6295 }
6296 prepared = true;
6297
6298 return 0;
6299}
6300
6301int RGWRados::Bucket::UpdateIndex::complete(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, int64_t poolid, uint64_t epoch,
6302 uint64_t size, uint64_t accounted_size,
6303 ceph::real_time& ut, const string& etag,
6304 const string& content_type, const string& storage_class,
6305 bufferlist *acl_bl,
6306 RGWObjCategory category,
6307 list<rgw_obj_index_key> *remove_objs, const string *user_data,
6308 bool appendable)
6309{
6310 if (blind) {
6311 return 0;
6312 }
6313 RGWRados *store = target->get_store();
6314 BucketShard *bs = nullptr;
6315
6316 int ret = get_bucket_shard(&bs, dpp);
6317 if (ret < 0) {
6318 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << "failed to get BucketShard object: ret=" << ret << dendl;
6319 return ret;
6320 }
6321
6322 rgw_bucket_dir_entry ent;
6323 obj.key.get_index_key(&ent.key);
6324 ent.meta.size = size;
6325 ent.meta.accounted_size = accounted_size;
6326 ent.meta.mtime = ut;
6327 ent.meta.etag = etag;
6328 ent.meta.storage_class = storage_class;
6329 if (user_data)
6330 ent.meta.user_data = *user_data;
6331
6332 ACLOwner owner;
6333 if (acl_bl && acl_bl->length()) {
6334 int ret = store->decode_policy(dpp, *acl_bl, &owner);
6335 if (ret < 0) {
6336 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "WARNING: could not decode policy ret=" << ret << dendl;
6337 }
6338 }
6339 ent.meta.owner = owner.get_id().to_str();
6340 ent.meta.owner_display_name = owner.get_display_name();
6341 ent.meta.content_type = content_type;
6342 ent.meta.appendable = appendable;
6343
6344 ret = store->cls_obj_complete_add(*bs, obj, optag, poolid, epoch, ent, category, remove_objs, bilog_flags, zones_trace);
6345
6346 int r = store->svc.datalog_rados->add_entry(dpp, target->bucket_info, bs->shard_id);
6347 if (r < 0) {
6348 ldpp_dout(dpp, -1) << "ERROR: failed writing data log" << dendl;
6349 }
6350
6351 return ret;
6352}
6353
6354int RGWRados::Bucket::UpdateIndex::complete_del(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
6355 int64_t poolid, uint64_t epoch,
6356 real_time& removed_mtime,
6357 list<rgw_obj_index_key> *remove_objs)
6358{
6359 if (blind) {
6360 return 0;
6361 }
6362 RGWRados *store = target->get_store();
6363 BucketShard *bs = nullptr;
6364
6365 int ret = get_bucket_shard(&bs, dpp);
6366 if (ret < 0) {
6367 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << "failed to get BucketShard object: ret=" << ret << dendl;
6368 return ret;
6369 }
6370
6371 ret = store->cls_obj_complete_del(*bs, optag, poolid, epoch, obj, removed_mtime, remove_objs, bilog_flags, zones_trace);
6372
6373 int r = store->svc.datalog_rados->add_entry(dpp, target->bucket_info, bs->shard_id);
6374 if (r < 0) {
6375 ldpp_dout(dpp, -1) << "ERROR: failed writing data log" << dendl;
6376 }
6377
6378 return ret;
6379}
6380
6381
6382int RGWRados::Bucket::UpdateIndex::cancel(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
6383 list<rgw_obj_index_key> *remove_objs)
6384{
6385 if (blind) {
6386 return 0;
6387 }
6388 RGWRados *store = target->get_store();
6389 BucketShard *bs;
6390
6391 int ret = guard_reshard(dpp, &bs, [&](BucketShard *bs) -> int {
6392 return store->cls_obj_complete_cancel(*bs, optag, obj, remove_objs, bilog_flags, zones_trace);
6393 });
6394
6395 /*
6396 * need to update data log anyhow, so that whoever follows needs to update its internal markers
6397 * for following the specific bucket shard log. Otherwise they end up staying behind, and users
6398 * have no way to tell that they're all caught up
6399 */
6400 int r = store->svc.datalog_rados->add_entry(dpp, target->bucket_info, bs->shard_id);
6401 if (r < 0) {
6402 ldpp_dout(dpp, -1) << "ERROR: failed writing data log" << dendl;
6403 }
6404
6405 return ret;
6406}
6407
6408int RGWRados::Object::Read::read(int64_t ofs, int64_t end, bufferlist& bl, optional_yield y, const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp)
6409{
6410 RGWRados *store = source->get_store();
6411
6412 rgw_raw_obj read_obj;
6413 uint64_t read_ofs = ofs;
6414 uint64_t len, read_len;
6415 bool reading_from_head = true;
6416 ObjectReadOperation op;
6417
6418 bool merge_bl = false;
6419 bufferlist *pbl = &bl;
6420 bufferlist read_bl;
6421 uint64_t max_chunk_size;
6422
6423 RGWObjState *astate;
6424 int r = source->get_state(dpp, &astate, true, y);
6425 if (r < 0)
6426 return r;
6427
6428 if (astate->size == 0) {
6429 end = 0;
6430 } else if (end >= (int64_t)astate->size) {
6431 end = astate->size - 1;
6432 }
6433
6434 if (end < 0)
6435 len = 0;
6436 else
6437 len = end - ofs + 1;
6438
6439 if (astate->manifest && astate->manifest->has_tail()) {
6440 /* now get the relevant object part */
6441 RGWObjManifest::obj_iterator iter = astate->manifest->obj_find(dpp, ofs);
6442
6443 uint64_t stripe_ofs = iter.get_stripe_ofs();
6444 read_obj = iter.get_location().get_raw_obj(store->store);
6445 len = std::min(len, iter.get_stripe_size() - (ofs - stripe_ofs));
6446 read_ofs = iter.location_ofs() + (ofs - stripe_ofs);
6447 reading_from_head = (read_obj == state.head_obj);
6448 } else {
6449 read_obj = state.head_obj;
6450 }
6451
6452 r = store->get_max_chunk_size(read_obj.pool, &max_chunk_size, dpp);
6453 if (r < 0) {
6454 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: failed to get max_chunk_size() for pool " << read_obj.pool << dendl;
6455 return r;
6456 }
6457
6458 if (len > max_chunk_size)
6459 len = max_chunk_size;
6460
6461
6462 read_len = len;
6463
6464 if (reading_from_head) {
6465 /* only when reading from the head object do we need to do the atomic test */
6466 r = store->append_atomic_test(dpp, &source->get_ctx(), source->get_bucket_info(), state.obj, op, &astate, y);
6467 if (r < 0)
6468 return r;
6469
6470 if (astate && astate->prefetch_data) {
6471 if (!ofs && astate->data.length() >= len) {
6472 bl = astate->data;
6473 return bl.length();
6474 }
6475
6476 if (ofs < astate->data.length()) {
6477 unsigned copy_len = std::min((uint64_t)astate->data.length() - ofs, len);
6478 astate->data.begin(ofs).copy(copy_len, bl);
6479 read_len -= copy_len;
6480 read_ofs += copy_len;
6481 if (!read_len)
6482 return bl.length();
6483
6484 merge_bl = true;
6485 pbl = &read_bl;
6486 }
6487 }
6488 }
6489
6490 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "rados->read obj-ofs=" << ofs << " read_ofs=" << read_ofs << " read_len=" << read_len << dendl;
6491 op.read(read_ofs, read_len, pbl, NULL);
6492
6493 if (state.cur_pool != read_obj.pool) {
6494 auto iter = state.io_ctxs.find(read_obj.pool);
6495 if (iter == state.io_ctxs.end()) {
6496 state.cur_ioctx = &state.io_ctxs[read_obj.pool];
6497 r = store->open_pool_ctx(dpp, read_obj.pool, *state.cur_ioctx, false);
6498 if (r < 0) {
6499 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "ERROR: failed to open pool context for pool=" << read_obj.pool << " r=" << r << dendl;
6500 return r;
6501 }
6502 } else {
6503 state.cur_ioctx = &iter->second;
6504 }
6505 state.cur_pool = read_obj.pool;
6506 }
6507
6508 state.cur_ioctx->locator_set_key(read_obj.loc);
6509
6510 r = state.cur_ioctx->operate(read_obj.oid, &op, NULL);
6511 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "rados->read r=" << r << " bl.length=" << bl.length() << dendl;
6512
6513 if (r < 0) {
6514 return r;
6515 }
6516
6517 if (merge_bl) {
6518 bl.append(read_bl);
6519 }
6520
6521 return bl.length();
6522}
6523
6524int get_obj_data::flush(rgw::AioResultList&& results) {
6525 int r = rgw::check_for_errors(results);
6526 if (r < 0) {
6527 return r;
6528 }
6529 std::list<bufferlist> bl_list;
6530
6531 auto cmp = [](const auto& lhs, const auto& rhs) { return lhs.id < rhs.id; };
6532 results.sort(cmp); // merge() requires results to be sorted first
6533 completed.merge(results, cmp); // merge results in sorted order
6534
6535 while (!completed.empty() && completed.front().id == offset) {
6536 auto bl = std::move(completed.front().data);
6537
6538 bl_list.push_back(bl);
6539 offset += bl.length();
6540 int r = client_cb->handle_data(bl, 0, bl.length());
6541 if (r < 0) {
6542 return r;
6543 }
6544
6545 if (rgwrados->get_use_datacache()) {
6546 const std::lock_guard l(d3n_get_data.d3n_lock);
6547 auto oid = completed.front().obj.get_ref().obj.oid;
6548 if (bl.length() <= g_conf()->rgw_get_obj_max_req_size && !d3n_bypass_cache_write) {
6549 lsubdout(g_ceph_context, rgw_datacache, 10) << "D3nDataCache: " << __func__ << "(): bl.length <= rgw_get_obj_max_req_size (default 4MB) - write to datacache, bl.length=" << bl.length() << dendl;
6550 rgwrados->d3n_data_cache->put(bl, bl.length(), oid);
6551 } else {
6552 lsubdout(g_ceph_context, rgw_datacache, 10) << "D3nDataCache: " << __func__ << "(): not writing to datacache - bl.length > rgw_get_obj_max_req_size (default 4MB), bl.length=" << bl.length() << " or d3n_bypass_cache_write=" << d3n_bypass_cache_write << dendl;
6553 }
6554 }
6555 completed.pop_front_and_dispose(std::default_delete<rgw::AioResultEntry>{});
6556 }
6557 return 0;
6558}
6559
6560static int _get_obj_iterate_cb(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
6561 const rgw_raw_obj& read_obj, off_t obj_ofs,
6562 off_t read_ofs, off_t len, bool is_head_obj,
6563 RGWObjState *astate, void *arg)
6564{
6565 struct get_obj_data* d = static_cast<struct get_obj_data*>(arg);
6566 return d->rgwrados->get_obj_iterate_cb(dpp, read_obj, obj_ofs, read_ofs, len,
6567 is_head_obj, astate, arg);
6568}
6569
6570int RGWRados::get_obj_iterate_cb(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
6571 const rgw_raw_obj& read_obj, off_t obj_ofs,
6572 off_t read_ofs, off_t len, bool is_head_obj,
6573 RGWObjState *astate, void *arg)
6574{
6575 ObjectReadOperation op;
6576 struct get_obj_data* d = static_cast<struct get_obj_data*>(arg);
6577 string oid, key;
6578
6579 if (is_head_obj) {
6580 /* only when reading from the head object do we need to do the atomic test */
6581 int r = append_atomic_test(dpp, astate, op);
6582 if (r < 0)
6583 return r;
6584
6585 if (astate &&
6586 obj_ofs < astate->data.length()) {
6587 unsigned chunk_len = std::min((uint64_t)astate->data.length() - obj_ofs, (uint64_t)len);
6588
6589 r = d->client_cb->handle_data(astate->data, obj_ofs, chunk_len);
6590 if (r < 0)
6591 return r;
6592
6593 len -= chunk_len;
6594 d->offset += chunk_len;
6595 read_ofs += chunk_len;
6596 obj_ofs += chunk_len;
6597 if (!len)
6598 return 0;
6599 }
6600 }
6601
6602 auto obj = d->rgwrados->svc.rados->obj(read_obj);
6603 int r = obj.open(dpp);
6604 if (r < 0) {
6605 ldpp_dout(dpp, 4) << "failed to open rados context for " << read_obj << dendl;
6606 return r;
6607 }
6608
6609 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "rados->get_obj_iterate_cb oid=" << read_obj.oid << " obj-ofs=" << obj_ofs << " read_ofs=" << read_ofs << " len=" << len << dendl;
6610 op.read(read_ofs, len, nullptr, nullptr);
6611
6612 const uint64_t cost = len;
6613 const uint64_t id = obj_ofs; // use logical object offset for sorting replies
6614
6615 auto completed = d->aio->get(obj, rgw::Aio::librados_op(std::move(op), d->yield), cost, id);
6616
6617 return d->flush(std::move(completed));
6618}
6619
6620int RGWRados::Object::Read::iterate(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, int64_t ofs, int64_t end, RGWGetDataCB *cb,
6621 optional_yield y)
6622{
6623 RGWRados *store = source->get_store();
6624 CephContext *cct = store->ctx();
6625 RGWObjectCtx& obj_ctx = source->get_ctx();
6626 const uint64_t chunk_size = cct->_conf->rgw_get_obj_max_req_size;
6627 const uint64_t window_size = cct->_conf->rgw_get_obj_window_size;
6628
6629 auto aio = rgw::make_throttle(window_size, y);
6630 get_obj_data data(store, cb, &*aio, ofs, y);
6631
6632 int r = store->iterate_obj(dpp, obj_ctx, source->get_bucket_info(), state.obj,
6633 ofs, end, chunk_size, _get_obj_iterate_cb, &data, y);
6634 if (r < 0) {
6635 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "iterate_obj() failed with " << r << dendl;
6636 data.cancel(); // drain completions without writing back to client
6637 return r;
6638 }
6639
6640 return data.drain();
6641}
6642
6643int RGWRados::iterate_obj(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWObjectCtx& obj_ctx,
6644 const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, const rgw_obj& obj,
6645 off_t ofs, off_t end, uint64_t max_chunk_size,
6646 iterate_obj_cb cb, void *arg, optional_yield y)
6647{
6648 rgw_raw_obj head_obj;
6649 rgw_raw_obj read_obj;
6650 uint64_t read_ofs = ofs;
6651 uint64_t len;
6652 bool reading_from_head = true;
6653 RGWObjState *astate = NULL;
6654
6655 obj_to_raw(bucket_info.placement_rule, obj, &head_obj);
6656
6657 int r = get_obj_state(dpp, &obj_ctx, bucket_info, obj, &astate, false, y);
6658 if (r < 0) {
6659 return r;
6660 }
6661
6662 if (end < 0)
6663 len = 0;
6664 else
6665 len = end - ofs + 1;
6666
6667 if (astate->manifest) {
6668 /* now get the relevant object stripe */
6669 RGWObjManifest::obj_iterator iter = astate->manifest->obj_find(dpp, ofs);
6670
6671 RGWObjManifest::obj_iterator obj_end = astate->manifest->obj_end(dpp);
6672
6673 for (; iter != obj_end && ofs <= end; ++iter) {
6674 off_t stripe_ofs = iter.get_stripe_ofs();
6675 off_t next_stripe_ofs = stripe_ofs + iter.get_stripe_size();
6676
6677 while (ofs < next_stripe_ofs && ofs <= end) {
6678 read_obj = iter.get_location().get_raw_obj(store);
6679 uint64_t read_len = std::min(len, iter.get_stripe_size() - (ofs - stripe_ofs));
6680 read_ofs = iter.location_ofs() + (ofs - stripe_ofs);
6681
6682 if (read_len > max_chunk_size) {
6683 read_len = max_chunk_size;
6684 }
6685
6686 reading_from_head = (read_obj == head_obj);
6687 r = cb(dpp, read_obj, ofs, read_ofs, read_len, reading_from_head, astate, arg);
6688 if (r < 0) {
6689 return r;
6690 }
6691
6692 len -= read_len;
6693 ofs += read_len;
6694 }
6695 }
6696 } else {
6697 while (ofs <= end) {
6698 read_obj = head_obj;
6699 uint64_t read_len = std::min(len, max_chunk_size);
6700
6701 r = cb(dpp, read_obj, ofs, ofs, read_len, reading_from_head, astate, arg);
6702 if (r < 0) {
6703 return r;
6704 }
6705
6706 len -= read_len;
6707 ofs += read_len;
6708 }
6709 }
6710
6711 return 0;
6712}
6713
6714int RGWRados::obj_operate(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, const rgw_obj& obj, ObjectWriteOperation *op)
6715{
6716 rgw_rados_ref ref;
6717 int r = get_obj_head_ref(dpp, bucket_info, obj, &ref);
6718 if (r < 0) {
6719 return r;
6720 }
6721
6722 return rgw_rados_operate(dpp, ref.pool.ioctx(), ref.obj.oid, op, null_yield);
6723}
6724
6725int RGWRados::obj_operate(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, const rgw_obj& obj, ObjectReadOperation *op)
6726{
6727 rgw_rados_ref ref;
6728 int r = get_obj_head_ref(dpp, bucket_info, obj, &ref);
6729 if (r < 0) {
6730 return r;
6731 }
6732
6733 bufferlist outbl;
6734
6735 return rgw_rados_operate(dpp, ref.pool.ioctx(), ref.obj.oid, op, &outbl, null_yield);
6736}
6737
6738int RGWRados::olh_init_modification_impl(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, RGWObjState& state, const rgw_obj& olh_obj, string *op_tag)
6739{
6740 ObjectWriteOperation op;
6741
6742 ceph_assert(olh_obj.key.instance.empty());
6743
6744 bool has_tag = (state.exists && has_olh_tag(state.attrset));
6745
6746 if (!state.exists) {
6747 op.create(true);
6748 } else {
6749 op.assert_exists();
6750 struct timespec mtime_ts = real_clock::to_timespec(state.mtime);
6751 op.mtime2(&mtime_ts);
6752 }
6753
6754 /*
6755 * 3 possible cases: olh object doesn't exist, it exists as an olh, it exists as a regular object.
6756 * If it exists as a regular object we'll need to transform it into an olh. We'll do it in two
6757 * steps, first change its tag and set the olh pending attrs. Once write is done we'll need to
6758 * truncate it, remove extra attrs, and send it to the garbage collection. The bucket index olh
6759 * log will reflect that.
6760 *
6761 * Need to generate separate olh and obj tags, as olh can be colocated with object data. obj_tag
6762 * is used for object data instance, olh_tag for olh instance.
6763 */
6764 if (has_tag) {
6765 /* guard against racing writes */
6766 bucket_index_guard_olh_op(dpp, state, op);
6767 }
6768
6769 if (!has_tag) {
6770 /* obj tag */
6771 string obj_tag = gen_rand_alphanumeric_lower(cct, 32);
6772
6773 bufferlist bl;
6774 bl.append(obj_tag.c_str(), obj_tag.size());
6775 op.setxattr(RGW_ATTR_ID_TAG, bl);
6776
6777 state.attrset[RGW_ATTR_ID_TAG] = bl;
6778 state.obj_tag = bl;
6779
6780 /* olh tag */
6781 string olh_tag = gen_rand_alphanumeric_lower(cct, 32);
6782
6783 bufferlist olh_bl;
6784 olh_bl.append(olh_tag.c_str(), olh_tag.size());
6785 op.setxattr(RGW_ATTR_OLH_ID_TAG, olh_bl);
6786
6787 state.attrset[RGW_ATTR_OLH_ID_TAG] = olh_bl;
6788 state.olh_tag = olh_bl;
6789 state.is_olh = true;
6790
6791 bufferlist verbl;
6792 op.setxattr(RGW_ATTR_OLH_VER, verbl);
6793 }
6794
6795 bufferlist bl;
6796 RGWOLHPendingInfo pending_info;
6797 pending_info.time = real_clock::now();
6798 encode(pending_info, bl);
6799
6800#define OLH_PENDING_TAG_LEN 32
6801 /* tag will start with current time epoch, this so that entries are sorted by time */
6802 char buf[32];
6803 utime_t ut(pending_info.time);
6804 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%016llx", (unsigned long long)ut.sec());
6805 *op_tag = buf;
6806
6807 string s = gen_rand_alphanumeric_lower(cct, OLH_PENDING_TAG_LEN - op_tag->size());
6808
6809 op_tag->append(s);
6810
6811 string attr_name = RGW_ATTR_OLH_PENDING_PREFIX;
6812 attr_name.append(*op_tag);
6813
6814 op.setxattr(attr_name.c_str(), bl);
6815
6816 int ret = obj_operate(dpp, bucket_info, olh_obj, &op);
6817 if (ret < 0) {
6818 return ret;
6819 }
6820
6821 state.exists = true;
6822 state.attrset[attr_name] = bl;
6823
6824 return 0;
6825}
6826
6827int RGWRados::olh_init_modification(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, RGWObjState& state, const rgw_obj& obj, string *op_tag)
6828{
6829 int ret;
6830
6831 ret = olh_init_modification_impl(dpp, bucket_info, state, obj, op_tag);
6832 if (ret == -EEXIST) {
6833 ret = -ECANCELED;
6834 }
6835
6836 return ret;
6837}
6838
6839int RGWRados::guard_reshard(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
6840 BucketShard *bs,
6841 const rgw_obj& obj_instance,
6842 const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info,
6843 std::function<int(BucketShard *)> call)
6844{
6845 rgw_obj obj;
6846 const rgw_obj *pobj = &obj_instance;
6847 int r;
6848
6849 for (int i = 0; i < NUM_RESHARD_RETRIES; ++i) {
6850 r = bs->init(pobj->bucket, *pobj, nullptr /* no RGWBucketInfo */, dpp);
6851 if (r < 0) {
6852 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << "bs.init() returned ret=" << r << dendl;
6853 return r;
6854 }
6855 r = call(bs);
6856 if (r != -ERR_BUSY_RESHARDING) {
6857 break;
6858 }
6859 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "NOTICE: resharding operation on bucket index detected, blocking" << dendl;
6860 string new_bucket_id;
6861 r = block_while_resharding(bs, &new_bucket_id, bucket_info, null_yield, dpp);
6862 if (r == -ERR_BUSY_RESHARDING) {
6863 continue;
6864 }
6865 if (r < 0) {
6866 return r;
6867 }
6868 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "reshard completion identified, new_bucket_id=" << new_bucket_id << dendl;
6869 i = 0; /* resharding is finished, make sure we can retry */
6870
6871 obj = *pobj;
6872 obj.bucket.update_bucket_id(new_bucket_id);
6873 pobj = &obj;
6874 } // for loop
6875
6876 if (r < 0) {
6877 return r;
6878 }
6879
6880 return 0;
6881}
6882
6883
6884int RGWRados::fetch_new_bucket_id(
6885 const RGWBucketInfo& curr_bucket_info,
6886 RGWBucketInfo* save_bucket_info, // nullptr -> no save
6887 std::string& new_bucket_id,
6888 const DoutPrefixProvider* dpp)
6889{
6890 RGWBucketInfo local_bucket_info; // use if save_bucket_info is null
6891 RGWBucketInfo* bip = save_bucket_info ? save_bucket_info : &local_bucket_info;
6892 *bip = curr_bucket_info; // copy
6893
6894 int ret = try_refresh_bucket_info(*bip, nullptr, dpp);
6895 if (ret < 0) {
6896 return ret;
6897 }
6898
6899 new_bucket_id = bip->bucket.bucket_id;
6900 return 0;
6901} // fetch_new_bucket_id
6902
6903
6904int RGWRados::block_while_resharding(RGWRados::BucketShard *bs,
6905 std::string *new_bucket_id,
6906 const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info,
6907 optional_yield y,
6908 const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp)
6909{
6910 int ret = 0;
6911 cls_rgw_bucket_instance_entry entry;
6912
6913 constexpr int num_retries = 10;
6914 for (int i = 1; i <= num_retries; i++) { // nb: 1-based for loop
6915 auto& ref = bs->bucket_obj.get_ref();
6916 ret = cls_rgw_get_bucket_resharding(ref.pool.ioctx(), ref.obj.oid, &entry);
6917 if (ret == -ENOENT) {
6918 ret = fetch_new_bucket_id(bucket_info, nullptr, *new_bucket_id, dpp);
6919 if (ret < 0) {
6920 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: " << __func__ <<
6921 " failed to refresh bucket info after reshard when get bucket "
6922 "resharding failed, error: " << cpp_strerror(-ret) << dendl;
6923 return ret;
6924 }
6925 } else if (ret < 0) {
6926 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << __func__ <<
6927 " ERROR: failed to get bucket resharding : " << cpp_strerror(-ret) <<
6928 dendl;
6929 return ret;
6930 }
6931
6932 if (!entry.resharding_in_progress()) {
6933 ret = fetch_new_bucket_id(bucket_info, nullptr, *new_bucket_id, dpp);
6934 if (ret < 0) {
6935 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: " << __func__ <<
6936 " failed to refresh bucket info after reshard when get bucket "
6937 "resharding succeeded, error: " << cpp_strerror(-ret) << dendl;
6938 return ret;
6939 }
6940 }
6941
6942 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "NOTICE: reshard still in progress; " <<
6943 (i < num_retries ? "retrying" : "too many retries") << dendl;
6944
6945 if (i == num_retries) {
6946 break;
6947 }
6948
6949 // If bucket is erroneously marked as resharding (e.g., crash or
6950 // other error) then fix it. If we can take the bucket reshard
6951 // lock then it means no other resharding should be taking place,
6952 // and we're free to clear the flags.
6953 {
6954 // since we expect to do this rarely, we'll do our work in a
6955 // block and erase our work after each try
6956
6957 RGWObjectCtx obj_ctx(this->store);
6958 const rgw_bucket& b = bs->bucket;
6959 std::string bucket_id = b.get_key();
6960 RGWBucketReshardLock reshard_lock(this->store, bucket_info, true);
6961 ret = reshard_lock.lock(dpp);
6962 if (ret == -ENOENT) {
6963 continue;
6964 } else if (ret < 0) {
6965 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ <<
6966 ": failed to take reshard lock for bucket " <<
6967 bucket_id << "; expected if resharding underway" << dendl;
6968 } else {
6969 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ <<
6970 ": was able to take reshard lock for bucket " <<
6971 bucket_id << dendl;
6972
6973 ret = RGWBucketReshard::clear_resharding(dpp, this->store, bucket_info);
6974 reshard_lock.unlock();
6975
6976 if (ret == -ENOENT) {
6977 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ <<
6978 " INFO: no need to reset reshard flags; old shards apparently"
6979 " removed after successful resharding of bucket " <<
6980 bucket_id << dendl;
6981 continue;
6982 } else if (ret < 0) {
6983 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ <<
6984 " ERROR: failed to clear resharding flags for bucket " <<
6985 bucket_id << ", " << cpp_strerror(-ret) << dendl;
6986 } else {
6987 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ <<
6988 ": apparently successfully cleared resharding flags for "
6989 "bucket " << bucket_id << dendl;
6990 continue; // if we apparently succeed immediately test again
6991 } // if clear resharding succeeded
6992 } // if taking of lock succeeded
6993 } // block to encapsulate recovery from incomplete reshard
6994
6995 ret = reshard_wait->wait(y);
6996 if (ret < 0) {
6997 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ <<
6998 " ERROR: bucket is still resharding, please retry" << dendl;
6999 return ret;
7000 }
7001 } // for loop
7002
7003 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ <<
7004 " ERROR: bucket is still resharding, please retry" << dendl;
7005 return -ERR_BUSY_RESHARDING;
7006}
7007
7008int RGWRados::bucket_index_link_olh(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, RGWObjState& olh_state, const rgw_obj& obj_instance,
7009 bool delete_marker,
7010 const string& op_tag,
7011 struct rgw_bucket_dir_entry_meta *meta,
7012 uint64_t olh_epoch,
7013 real_time unmod_since, bool high_precision_time,
7014 rgw_zone_set *_zones_trace, bool log_data_change)
7015{
7016 rgw_rados_ref ref;
7017 int r = get_obj_head_ref(dpp, bucket_info, obj_instance, &ref);
7018 if (r < 0) {
7019 return r;
7020 }
7021
7022 rgw_zone_set zones_trace;
7023 if (_zones_trace) {
7024 zones_trace = *_zones_trace;
7025 }
7026 zones_trace.insert(svc.zone->get_zone().id, bucket_info.bucket.get_key());
7027
7028 BucketShard bs(this);
7029
7030 r = guard_reshard(dpp, &bs, obj_instance, bucket_info,
7031 [&](BucketShard *bs) -> int {
7032 cls_rgw_obj_key key(obj_instance.key.get_index_key_name(), obj_instance.key.instance);
7033 auto& ref = bs->bucket_obj.get_ref();
7034 librados::ObjectWriteOperation op;
7035 op.assert_exists(); // bucket index shard must exist
7036 cls_rgw_guard_bucket_resharding(op, -ERR_BUSY_RESHARDING);
7037 cls_rgw_bucket_link_olh(op, key, olh_state.olh_tag,
7038 delete_marker, op_tag, meta, olh_epoch,
7039 unmod_since, high_precision_time,
7040 svc.zone->get_zone().log_data, zones_trace);
7041 return rgw_rados_operate(dpp, ref.pool.ioctx(), ref.obj.oid, &op, null_yield);
7042 });
7043 if (r < 0) {
7044 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "rgw_rados_operate() after cls_rgw_bucket_link_olh() returned r=" << r << dendl;
7045 return r;
7046 }
7047
7048 r = svc.datalog_rados->add_entry(dpp, bucket_info, bs.shard_id);
7049 if (r < 0) {
7050 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "ERROR: failed writing data log" << dendl;
7051 }
7052
7053 return 0;
7054}
7055
7056void RGWRados::bucket_index_guard_olh_op(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWObjState& olh_state, ObjectOperation& op)
7057{
7058 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << __func__ << "(): olh_state.olh_tag=" << string(olh_state.olh_tag.c_str(), olh_state.olh_tag.length()) << dendl;
7059 op.cmpxattr(RGW_ATTR_OLH_ID_TAG, CEPH_OSD_CMPXATTR_OP_EQ, olh_state.olh_tag);
7060}

7062int RGWRados::bucket_index_unlink_instance(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, const rgw_obj& obj_instance,
7063 const string& op_tag, const string& olh_tag, uint64_t olh_epoch, rgw_zone_set *_zones_trace)
7064{
7065 rgw_rados_ref ref;
7066 int r = get_obj_head_ref(dpp, bucket_info, obj_instance, &ref);
7067 if (r < 0) {
7068 return r;
7069 }
7070
7071 rgw_zone_set zones_trace;
7072 if (_zones_trace) {
7073 zones_trace = *_zones_trace;
7074 }
7075 zones_trace.insert(svc.zone->get_zone().id, bucket_info.bucket.get_key());
7076
7077 BucketShard bs(this);
7078
7079 cls_rgw_obj_key key(obj_instance.key.get_index_key_name(), obj_instance.key.instance);
7080 r = guard_reshard(dpp, &bs, obj_instance, bucket_info,
7081 [&](BucketShard *bs) -> int {
7082 auto& ref = bs->bucket_obj.get_ref();
7083 librados::ObjectWriteOperation op;
7084 op.assert_exists(); // bucket index shard must exist
7085 cls_rgw_guard_bucket_resharding(op, -ERR_BUSY_RESHARDING);
7086 cls_rgw_bucket_unlink_instance(op, key, op_tag,
7087 olh_tag, olh_epoch, svc.zone->get_zone().log_data, zones_trace);
7088 return rgw_rados_operate(dpp, ref.pool.ioctx(), ref.obj.oid, &op, null_yield);
7089 });
7090 if (r < 0) {
7091 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "rgw_rados_operate() after cls_rgw_bucket_link_instance() returned r=" << r << dendl;
7092 return r;
7093 }
7094
7095 return 0;
7096}
7097
7098int RGWRados::bucket_index_read_olh_log(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
7099 const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, RGWObjState& state,
7100 const rgw_obj& obj_instance, uint64_t ver_marker,
7101 map<uint64_t, vector<rgw_bucket_olh_log_entry> > *log,
7102 bool *is_truncated)
7103{
7104 rgw_rados_ref ref;
7105 int r = get_obj_head_ref(dpp, bucket_info, obj_instance, &ref);
7106 if (r < 0) {
7107 return r;
7108 }
7109
7110 BucketShard bs(this);
7111 int ret =
7112 bs.init(obj_instance.bucket, obj_instance, nullptr /* no RGWBucketInfo */, dpp);
7113 if (ret < 0) {
7114 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << "bs.init() returned ret=" << ret << dendl;
7115 return ret;
7116 }
7117
7118 string olh_tag(state.olh_tag.c_str(), state.olh_tag.length());
7119
7120 cls_rgw_obj_key key(obj_instance.key.get_index_key_name(), string());
7121
7122 auto& shard_ref = bs.bucket_obj.get_ref();
7123 ObjectReadOperation op;
7124
7125 rgw_cls_read_olh_log_ret log_ret;
7126 int op_ret = 0;
7127 cls_rgw_get_olh_log(op, key, ver_marker, olh_tag, log_ret, op_ret);
7128 bufferlist outbl;
7129 r = rgw_rados_operate(dpp, shard_ref.pool.ioctx(), shard_ref.obj.oid, &op, &outbl, null_yield);
7130 if (r < 0) {
7131 return r;
7132 }
7133 if (op_ret < 0) {
7134 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "cls_rgw_get_olh_log() returned op_ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
7135 return op_ret;
7136 }
7137
7138 *log = std::move(log_ret.log);
7139 *is_truncated = log_ret.is_truncated;
7140
7141 return 0;
7142}
7143
7144// a multisite sync bug resulted in the OLH head attributes being overwritten by
7145// the attributes from another zone, causing link_olh() to fail endlessly due to
7146// olh_tag mismatch. this attempts to detect this case and reconstruct the OLH
7147// attributes from the bucket index. see http://tracker.ceph.com/issues/37792
7148int RGWRados::repair_olh(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, RGWObjState* state, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info,
7149 const rgw_obj& obj)
7150{
7151 // fetch the current olh entry from the bucket index
7152 rgw_bucket_olh_entry olh;
7153 int r = bi_get_olh(dpp, bucket_info, obj, &olh);
7154 if (r < 0) {
7155 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "repair_olh failed to read olh entry for " << obj << dendl;
7156 return r;
7157 }
7158 if (olh.tag == rgw_bl_str(state->olh_tag)) { // mismatch already resolved?
7159 return 0;
7160 }
7161
7162 ldpp_dout(dpp, 4) << "repair_olh setting olh_tag=" << olh.tag
7163 << " key=" << olh.key << " delete_marker=" << olh.delete_marker << dendl;
7164
7165 // rewrite OLH_ID_TAG and OLH_INFO from current olh
7166 ObjectWriteOperation op;
7167 // assert this is the same olh tag we think we're fixing
7168 bucket_index_guard_olh_op(dpp, *state, op);
7169 // preserve existing mtime
7170 struct timespec mtime_ts = ceph::real_clock::to_timespec(state->mtime);
7171 op.mtime2(&mtime_ts);
7172 {
7173 bufferlist bl;
7174 bl.append(olh.tag.c_str(), olh.tag.size());
7175 op.setxattr(RGW_ATTR_OLH_ID_TAG, bl);
7176 }
7177 {
7178 RGWOLHInfo info;
7179 info.target = rgw_obj(bucket_info.bucket, olh.key);
7180 info.removed = olh.delete_marker;
7181 bufferlist bl;
7182 encode(info, bl);
7183 op.setxattr(RGW_ATTR_OLH_INFO, bl);
7184 }
7185 rgw_rados_ref ref;
7186 r = get_obj_head_ref(dpp, bucket_info, obj, &ref);
7187 if (r < 0) {
7188 return r;
7189 }
7190 r = rgw_rados_operate(dpp, ref.pool.ioctx(), ref.obj.oid, &op, null_yield);
7191 if (r < 0) {
7192 ldpp_dout(dpp, 0) << "repair_olh failed to write olh attributes with "
7193 << cpp_strerror(r) << dendl;
7194 return r;
7195 }
7196 return 0;
7197}
7198
7199int RGWRados::bucket_index_trim_olh_log(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, const RGWBucketInfo& bucket_info, RGWObjState& state, const rgw_obj& obj_instance, uint64_t ver)
7200{
7201 rgw_rados_ref ref;
7202 int r = get_obj_head_ref(dpp, bucket_info, obj_instance, &ref);
7203 if (r < 0) {
7204 return r;
7205 }
7206
7207 BucketShard bs(this);
7208 int ret =
7209 bs.init(obj_instance.bucket, obj_instance, nullptr /* no RGWBucketInfo */, dpp);
7210 if (ret < 0) {
7211 ldpp_dout(dpp, 5) << "bs.init() returned ret=" << ret << dendl;
7212 return ret;
7213 }
7214
7215 string olh_tag(state.olh_tag.c_str(), state.olh_tag.length());
7216
7217 cls_rgw_obj_key key(obj_instance.key.get_index_key_name(), string());
7218
7219 ret = guard_reshard(dpp, &bs, obj_instance, bucket_info,
7220 [&](BucketShard *pbs) -> int {
7221 ObjectWriteOperation op;
7222 op.assert_exists(); // bucket index shard must exist
7223 cls_rgw_guard_bucket_resharding(op, -ERR_BUSY_RESHARDING);
7224 cls_rgw_trim_olh_log(op, key, ver, olh_tag);
7225 return pbs->bucket_obj.operate(dpp, &op, null_yield);
7226 });
7227 if (ret < 0) {
7228 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "cls_rgw_trim_olh_log() returned r=" << ret << dendl;
7229 return ret;
7230 }
7231
7232 return 0;
7233}
